That screenshot is from a Table API account. You are using the SQL API SDK. 

If you want to use a Table API account, you would need to use the [Microsoft.Azure.Cosmos.Table](https://www.nuget.org/packages/Microsoft.Azure.Cosmos.Table) SDK (for .NET, there are [SDKs for other languages](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/cosmos-db/table-introduction#next-steps)). In that SDK, you can create tables like so:

    CloudStorageAccount storageAccount = CreateStorageAccountFromConnectionString(storageConnectionString);

    CloudTableClient tableClient = storageAccount.CreateCloudTableClient(new TableClientConfiguration());

    CloudTable table = tableClient.GetTableReference(&quot;order_details&quot;);
    if (await table.CreateIfNotExistsAsync())
    {
      Console.WriteLine(&quot;Created Table named: order_details&quot;);
    }
    else
    {
      Console.WriteLine(&quot;Table order_details already exists&quot;);
    }

If you don&#39;t need to work with the Tables API, you can create a SQL API account and use the code you already have.

Extracting the body of the BadRequest response will probably show you the reason for that request to have failed, which might point to the fact that you are mixing the SQL API SDK with a Tables API account.

